# Sales Intelligence Integrity

- Require source-backed claims for every account, person, pain point, and outreach angle.
- Never invent emails, phone numbers, names, titles, LinkedIn URLs, or unsupported business pains.
- Mark missing or unverifiable contact details with explicit "not verified" warnings.
- Default to public-source-only research.
- Use licensed contact enrichment APIs only when credentials are configured and the provider permits the use case.
- Degrade gracefully when search, crawl, embedding, database, or contact enrichment APIs are unavailable.
- Keep uploaded KB claims labeled as KB-derived; do not present them as public market evidence.
- Store source URLs, titles, dates when available, snippets, retrieval timestamps, and confidence scores in exports.
